Exclusions & Limitations

Client: 149296 Testing Nebraska Client | SubClient: 0001 Testing Nebraska Client - Actives
Subscriber | All Plans

Preventive:

Prophylaxes (cleanings) are payable twice per calendar year.

Fluoride treatments are payable once per calendar year for age 18 and under.

Space maintainers are payable once per area in a lifetime, for missing posterior, primary teeth, for age 16 and under.

Minor Restorative:

Amalgam and composite resin restorations are payable once within a 24-month period, regardless of the number or combination of restorations placed on a surface.

Composite resin (white) restorations on a posterior tooth is not covered and the Plan will pay only the applicable amount that it would have paid for an amalgam restoration.

Relines and Repairs:

Sealants:

Sealants are payable for first and second permanent molars for age 15 and under, limited to once per tooth per lifetime.

Other Oral Surgery:

All Other Radiographs:

Full mouth x-rays (which include bitewing x-rays) or a panorex are payable once in a five-year period.

Simple Extractions:

Bitewing Radiographs:

Bitewing x-rays are payable once per calendar year.

Periodontics:

Occlusal guards are not covered by the dental plan.

Root planing and scaling is payable once per quadrant in 24 consecutive months.

Endodontics:

Orthodontic Services:

Brush Biopsy:

TMD:

Diagnostic:

Oral examinations, including emergency examinations and examinations by a specialist, are payable twice in a calendar year.

Implants:

Implants and/or the restorations are payable once per tooth per five-year period.

Payment will not be made to replace a tooth that has been missing prior to the effective date of the coverage until the member has been eligible for 24 consecutive months.

Prosthodontics:

Fixed and removable prosthetic procedures are benefits once per ten-year period.

Bridgework is limited to once in a ten year period.

Payment will not be made to replace a tooth that has been missing prior to the effective date of the coverage until the member has been eligible for 24 consecutive months.

Major Restorative:

Crowns and onlays are limited to once per tooth in a ten-year period.

Inlays are covered benefits.

Posterior porcelain or resin crowns are covered benefits.

Other Basic Services:
